abstract: DuPont Company reports third-quarter profit, with net income climbing 23 percent, to $452 million, or 48 cents a share, from $367 million, or 40 cents a share, a year earlier; shares fall 2.5 percent, to $44.94.
snippet: The leading American chemical maker, which has exceeded expectations for the last 11 quarters, also raised its full-year forecast.
lead_paragraph: The leading American chemical maker, which has exceeded expectations for the last 11 quarters, also raised its full-year forecast.

headline.main: DuPont Earnings Continue to Surpass Analysts’ Expectations
